&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and committed Dietitian to join our busy and friendly Hospital team which is part of a larger dynamic Dietetic team. If you are looking for a part time position which will help you gain experience in acute dietetics then this is the post for you. Clinical duties involve working across a variety of wards including acute medical and elderly wards/ Clinic . We are looking for a team member with good communication skills who can demonstrate innovative approaches to patient education and counselling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based at Ealing Hospital a busy friendly general hospital situated in west London with a diverse patient population. We are a recognised department for dietetic student training for Placement 1, 2, and 3 .You will be expected to supervise Dietetic students and support staff&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We offer both departmental and personal CPD time to support your development and are committed to the development of evidenced based practice and clinical audit. You will be supported in attending relevant professional networking meetings, interest groups&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
